From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: James Dumay <jameswdumay@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 07:56:14 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] Import buun TCQ KV cache support

Add the TurboQuant TCQ KV cache types that produced the Qwen3.6 local
decode win, including the mixed Metal K/V path needed for:

    -ctk turbo3_tcq -ctv turbo2_tcq

Provenance:
- Source fork: https://github.com/spiritbuun/buun-llama-cpp
- Source checkout: /tmp/buun-llama-cpp at 65ada42cf97ca771cff8bad0923ce8ae41a13378
- Upstream base in this repo: 9725a313be0528214c4a02fed906ddaf7b3f712e
- Local benchmark patch: /Volumes/External/llama-stage-runtime-bench/qwen36-lab/buun-tcq-full-corpus-20260501-180404/buun-local-diff.patch
- Benchmark run root: /Volumes/External/llama-stage-runtime-bench/qwen36-lab/buun-tcq-full-corpus-20260501-180404

Port notes:
- Preserve this repo's pinned upstream q1_0 enum/type plumbing while adding the TurboQuant types after it.
- Keep the TCQ/TurboQuant KV, Metal, CUDA, and llama cache changes needed for the measured mixed K/V path.
- Exclude the buun fork's DFlash/context API surface from this patch; DFlash remains a separate research lane.

Measured package candidate:
- Qwen3.6 local OpenAI full-corpus sweep, 819/819 successful requests, zero errors
- Best setting: -ctk turbo3_tcq -ctv turbo2_tcq
- Weighted completion throughput: 32.02 tok/s, 1.167x vs turbo2
- Long-context corpus: 12.83 tok/s, 1.57x vs turbo2

This patch is intentionally imported as a fork-provenance patch rather than
rewritten from scratch so future rebases can compare it against the buun
implementation and the saved benchmark diff.
